The paper discusses the use of multi-agent systems and declarative logic programming for information retrieval and integration, which are topics that are commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses knowledge representation methods, which are relevant to logic (cs.LO) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper mentions natural language processing (cs.CL) as a potential application domain for the discussed methods.
